00:42.802 --> 00:45.242
Early relief.
So get the fuck out of here.

00:45.910 --> 00:47.941
Jesus, Bunk.
What time is it?

00:48.196 --> 00:49.182
4:30.

00:49.575 --> 00:52.374
I couldn't sleep, so
get the fuck gone.

00:53.313 --> 00:55.107
what time did Mcnulty
leave last night?

00:55.267 --> 00:57.338
Never did.
He's in number one.

00:57.498 --> 00:59.583
Pulling his hair out
over some shit.

01:10.396 --> 01:12.240
Think again about what
the fuck you're doing.

01:12.400 --> 01:14.184
Bunk, this can work.

01:15.101 --> 01:16.066
It can.

01:16.444 --> 01:18.440
Fuck you. I mean that.

01:20.117 --> 01:21.741
4:00 in the fuckin' morning?

01:22.270 --> 01:23.541
Oh, so it is.

01:27.200 --> 01:28.622
All of these?

01:29.126 --> 01:30.913
Homeless murders
from the last 5 years.

01:31.913 --> 01:35.288
Everything before that is on microfilm,
but we got enough right here

01:35.828 --> 01:37.044
Most of it open.

01:37.204 --> 01:39.376
We don't do so well
with homeless kilings.

01:39.535 --> 01:41.611
Transient locales,
no nearest, no dearest.

01:41.771 --> 01:44.385
No one gives a fuck.
Cases stay open forever.

01:45.041 --> 01:47.805
- You're going to jail behind this shit.
- Yes, you are.

01:48.368 --> 01:50.308
You know what they do
to police in jail?

01:50.582 --> 01:52.560
Pretty police like yourself?
Motherfucker,

01:52.861 --> 01:55.033
We have kids.
Houses.

01:55.647 --> 01:57.197
Car payments.
Furniture.

01:58.053 --> 01:59.886
I just bought brand-new lawn chairs

02:00.046 --> 02:02.642
and a glass patio table.
You don't buy no shit like that if you

02:02.802 --> 02:04.517
plan to lose your job
and go to prison.

02:04.677 --> 02:06.861
- You won't even get past the m.e.
- Watch me.

02:07.021 --> 02:09.476
You're dumping murders on us
that we can't solve.

02:09.636 --> 02:13.010
- You're fucking our clearance rate.
- Fuck the fucking numbers already.

02:13.404 --> 02:15.625
The fucking numbers destroyed
this fucking department.

02:16.002 --> 02:18.334
Landsman and his clearance
rate can suck a hairy asshole.

02:18.494 --> 02:20.136
Marlo ain't worth it.
Nobody is.

02:20.296 --> 02:21.678
Marlo's an asshole.

02:22.433 --> 02:24.468
He does not get to win.
We get to win.

02:24.828 --> 02:26.079
This case doesn't go away

02:26.239 --> 02:28.513
just because the bosses
can't find the money to pay for it.

02:28.673 --> 02:32.050
These are fucking murders--
Ghetto murders, but still,

02:33.088 --> 02:35.078
I came back out of the western
to work this case

02:35.238 --> 02:36.811
because they said it would be worked.

02:36.971 --> 02:40.134
I came back out on a promise,
and they're gonna keep that promise.

02:40.694 --> 02:42.175
Whether they know it or not.

02:42.565 --> 02:43.779
I'm gonna tell landsman.

02:44.892 --> 02:46.616
Yeah. You keep on with it,

02:46.776 --> 02:48.242
I'm gonna rat you out.

02:49.369 --> 02:51.116
You do what you got to do.

02:55.158 --> 02:57.263
My name is
nowhere in the file.

02:57.423 --> 02:59.529
I don't want fuck to do with this.

03:04.126 --> 03:05.133
Hey, Bunk.

05:08.852 --> 05:10.268
What're you doing?

05:10.428 --> 05:13.285
Final is out.
I want to see my story.

05:13.445 --> 05:14.229
Now?

05:14.389 --> 05:16.278
It's my first time out front.
I want to see it.

05:16.540 --> 05:18.223
This is why we should
get home delivery.

05:18.383 --> 05:21.393
Why pay for it when I get
it for free at the office?

05:23.662 --> 05:24.715
Be back.

05:34.087 --> 05:35.293
Brother ray.

05:36.646 --> 05:37.895
God rest ye.

06:25.700 --> 06:27.130
When does the "sun" get here?

06:28.200 --> 06:29.548
Around now usually.

08:08.974 --> 08:11.027
- Anybody got a working car?
- I got one,

08:11.187 --> 08:13.962
but I'm going back out
to my crime scene for a canvass.

08:14.297 --> 08:15.613
Drop me at the m.e.?

08:18.863 --> 08:20.442
My office now.

08:23.405 --> 08:25.840
I'll get a lift over
from one of the central cars.

08:31.253 --> 08:33.732
This is way past any shit
you ever pulled in your life.

08:33.892 --> 08:35.802
- Think on it.
- You see Greggs out there,

08:36.441 --> 08:37.774
bagging evidence alone,

08:37.933 --> 08:39.794
then going back out
to recanvass on a triple?

08:39.953 --> 08:42.517
A triple fucking murder.
A home invasion,

08:43.106 --> 08:44.747
and she's working it alone.

08:44.907 --> 08:47.397
They pulled Crutchfield this morning,
put him back in the rotation.

08:47.557 --> 08:50.050
- That's on them, but you can't--
- Fucking right, that's on them.

08:50.210 --> 08:51.191
A triple murder,

08:51.351 --> 08:54.782
and 12 hours later
they leave one detective alone on it?

08:54.942 --> 08:56.634
I guess she's lucky
she has a car.

08:57.358 --> 08:59.753
- This shit won't work.
- Then we're no worse than before.

09:00.201 --> 09:03.103
- Extra red name or two on the board.
- Yeah, unless you got caught.

09:03.263 --> 09:05.165
Who in this fucking unit
is gonna catch me?

09:05.325 --> 09:08.251
Most of the guys up here couldn't catch
the clap in a mexican whorehouse.

09:09.780 --> 09:11.172
What's with the red ribbon?

09:12.340 --> 09:16.047
Barlow had an open strangle
a few years back.

09:16.723 --> 09:19.179
Homeless guy with a red ribbon
tied around his wrist.

09:19.587 --> 09:20.881
So that's two.

09:21.211 --> 09:25.137
Also, I found an open homeless
case which Ray Cole worked.

09:25.700 --> 09:28.281
I wrote a ribbon
into his office reports.

09:28.516 --> 09:31.527
- So there's 3.
- Our guy didn't have a red ribbon.

09:34.168 --> 09:35.967
- That's where I'm headed.
- Jesus.

09:37.499 --> 09:39.325
- Listen to yourself.
- Upstairs

09:39.485 --> 09:42.322
wouldn't jump on a real serial killer--
fuckin' Marlo,

09:42.482 --> 09:44.249
who's got bodies all over hi

09:44.409 --> 09:45.882
maybe they need the make-believe.

09:46.042 --> 09:48.614
Yeah, maybe you're the asshole
just lost his fucking mind.

10:05.031 --> 10:07.066
- Crutchfield.
- Yeah, I'm locked in the box.

10:07.226 --> 10:09.309
- In the box?
- It's no joke. Let me out.

10:09.469 --> 10:10.630
Be right there.

10:17.667 --> 10:18.698
He fuck you?

10:20.563 --> 10:21.594
He tried...

10:23.276 --> 10:24.996
But mostly he just fucks himself.

10:29.239 --> 10:31.215
You ain't seen those yet, huh?

10:31.375 --> 10:33.004
I'll bet you didn't.

10:33.276 --> 10:36.484
Fucking Burrell's asshole
must be so tight

10:37.019 --> 10:40.223
you couldn't pull a pin from it
with a John Deere tractor.

10:41.392 --> 10:44.396
Here you're promising
a double-digit drop,

10:44.793 --> 10:46.059
and he gives you

10:46.514 --> 10:48.049
a 4% bump

10:48.430 --> 10:50.022
for two quarters in a row.

10:50.182 --> 10:51.742
Thanks for bringing these by, Stan.

10:51.949 --> 10:53.923
Well, I wanted to
give you a heads up.

10:54.844 --> 10:57.529
Truth is,
looking at numbers like those,

10:58.014 --> 11:00.610
I'm thinking you could do a lot worse

11:00.865 --> 11:03.619
than give me a run
as acting commissioner.

11:04.243 --> 11:05.936
I know you couldn't make me permanent.

11:06.477 --> 11:07.832
maybe 6 months

11:08.293 --> 11:11.342
while you keep grooming
your boy Daniels.

11:12.739 --> 11:14.326
I'd get a pension bump,

11:14.735 --> 11:18.208
and you'd get a head start
on clearing out deadwood,

11:18.611 --> 11:21.727
beginning with Burrell
and Rawls.

11:22.376 --> 11:25.058
Thanks, Stan.
Let me think on it.

11:25.737 --> 11:27.097
You do that, Tommy.

11:35.866 --> 11:38.301
Even on an acting basis,
can you imagine

11:38.461 --> 11:42.316
Nerese and the Ministers dealing
with commissioner Valchek?

11:43.492 --> 11:45.183
What are you gonna do
about the numbers?

11:45.343 --> 11:48.684
Fuck can I do? I cut the department
budget to the bone, right?

11:49.020 --> 11:51.351
Can't very well complain
when the crime rate bumps.

11:51.680 --> 11:54.504
Burrell comes in here
and owns these,

11:54.817 --> 11:56.119
I got to give him a pass--

11:56.279 --> 11:58.508
at least until I can fix
his money problems.

12:02.429 --> 12:04.572
Your piece took a bad bite there.

12:04.732 --> 12:06.377
35 inches down to 12?

12:06.633 --> 12:09.784
Yeah, well, it's my fault
for giving it up to the a-section.

12:10.097 --> 12:11.771
Page one editor made
noises like it was

12:11.931 --> 12:13.640
gonna go out front. Then he...

12:13.800 --> 12:16.412
ossed it back to metro
before the double-dot.

12:16.756 --> 12:19.321
Night editor didn't have room
to take it back, so...

12:19.858 --> 12:21.613
Story deserved better. Sorry.

12:23.078 --> 12:24.891
3 people murdered in a house,

12:25.121 --> 12:27.468
and it gets 12 inches below the fold.

12:28.341 --> 12:30.717
- Explain that to me.
- There's no explaining it.

12:31.103 --> 12:32.251
Advertising's down,

12:32.742 --> 12:35.052
we got a smaller news hole,
we're not managing it well.

12:35.534 --> 12:36.785
We messed up.

12:37.227 --> 12:38.302
That's all.

12:44.158 --> 12:45.299
Wrong zip code.

12:46.392 --> 12:48.251
They're dead where it doesn't count.

12:48.821 --> 12:51.289
If they were white
and murdered in Tmonium,

12:51.449 --> 12:53.079
you'd have had 30 inches off the front.

12:53.239 --> 12:55.775
Would have been my first front-pager
where I didn't share a byline.

12:56.424 --> 12:57.359
Yeah?

12:58.866 --> 13:02.615
I drove down to the port covington plant
this morning to get a copy.

13:02.775 --> 13:04.825
Well, you ain't the first to do that.

13:07.547 --> 13:09.334
Our 10-7 on e floor yet?

13:09.494 --> 13:11.232
He's by the overhead camera.

13:11.837 --> 13:13.584
I need to grab prints,
get him I.D.ed.

13:13.744 --> 13:16.709
Don't you want to wait for the post,
keep his hands clean for trace?

13:16.869 --> 13:19.882
I need to know who my victim is.
That's the priority.

13:20.876 --> 13:23.511
Finish your breakfast.
I got plenty of time.

14:09.995 --> 14:12.540
There's nothing under the nails
that I can see.

14:12.700 --> 14:14.323
I think we can risk prints.

14:29.799 --> 14:30.788
Something's up.

14:31.686 --> 14:33.040
Please. Gather around.

14:35.631 --> 14:38.504
Steve, could someone get word
across the hall to features and sports?

14:38.664 --> 14:40.171
We want everyone on this.

14:48.716 --> 14:50.487
What, did we get sold again?

14:51.316 --> 14:53.682
First the "L.A. Times" buys us up,
then the "Tribune."

14:53.842 --> 14:54.854
Law of the fish.

14:55.184 --> 14:57.400
- We're the minnow.
- Maybe we won a Pulitzer.

14:57.560 --> 14:59.285
Pulitzers are still a week away.

14:59.445 --> 15:00.813
It just turned April.

15:02.422 --> 15:03.945
Look at Whiting's pants.

15:04.747 --> 15:08.670
If we won a Pulitzer,
the executive editor would be tumescent.

15:09.446 --> 15:10.481
Toom-what?

15:10.641 --> 15:12.664
Speak English.
I'm just a police reporter.

15:12.823 --> 15:14.794
Tumescent. Engorged.

15:15.281 --> 15:16.331
Exactly.

15:16.491 --> 15:19.932
It's a bad time for newspapers,
as you all know.

15:20.914 --> 15:22.663
The news hole is shrinking

15:23.233 --> 15:26.050
as advertising dollars
continue to decline.

15:26.503 --> 15:29.597
Our circulation numbers
are also down as we compete with a

15:30.055 --> 15:31.503
variety of media.

15:32.083 --> 15:34.695
Technology is driving distribution,

15:36.428 --> 15:37.678
and the Internet

15:38.287 --> 15:41.088
is a free source of news and opinions.

15:41.421 --> 15:44.273
Seeking a balance in this new world,

15:45.458 --> 15:47.421
we're now faced with hard choices.

15:48.359 --> 15:52.447
We opened our first foreign
bureau in London in 1924.

15:53.147 --> 15:57.769
The "Sun's" foreign coverage
has been a source of pride ever since.

15:59.979 --> 16:01.361
So it is with

16:02.963 --> 16:04.337
tremendous regret

16:05.785 --> 16:09.494
that I tell you that Chicago
has made it clear that the bureaus

16:09.800 --> 16:10.990
in Beijing,

16:11.516 --> 16:15.488
Moscow, Jerusalem,
Johannesburg, and London

16:16.148 --> 16:17.593
will all be shuttered.

16:19.327 --> 16:21.084
Elsewhere in the newsroom,

16:22.093 --> 16:24.194
there will be
a fresh round of buyouts.

16:25.243 --> 16:27.532
Chicago has given us some specific

16:27.774 --> 16:29.015
budgetary targets

16:29.409 --> 16:31.743
that will require some hard choices

16:31.903 --> 16:33.575
throughout the newsroom.

16:33.961 --> 16:35.497
We are, quite simply,

16:36.737 --> 16:39.959
going to have to find ways
to do more with less.

16:40.414 --> 16:43.255
So I guess I will
turn this over to tom,

16:43.802 --> 16:45.799
who will get into the specifics.

16:48.327 --> 16:49.800
I know some of you have questions.

16:49.960 --> 16:52.598
If you could hold them for me
until after I've had a chance to speak.

16:52.949 --> 16:55.159
Pull your clipbook together.
Time to find a new home.

16:55.319 --> 16:56.581
Chicago has sent us a memo

16:56.741 --> 16:58.854
outlining options that are
available to those of you...

16:59.142 --> 17:02.074
The aorta should have elasticity to it,

17:02.234 --> 17:03.317
t it's rock hard.

17:03.649 --> 17:07.021
Whoever strangled him could've
just waited a month or two more.

17:07.457 --> 17:08.823
This guy was on his last legs.

17:09.281 --> 17:10.488
It is what it is.

17:10.982 --> 17:13.198
In addition to the fractured hyoid
and the bruising,

17:13.358 --> 17:15.281
I got signs of a struggle
around the body,

17:15.518 --> 17:16.777
a couple witnesses

17:16.936 --> 17:19.893
who thought they heard sounds
of a struggle inside the house.

17:20.571 --> 17:22.700
Also that ribbon you snipped off,

17:23.482 --> 17:24.789
it might tie to other cases.

17:24.949 --> 17:27.523
The ribbon my own investigator
missed at the scene.

17:27.684 --> 17:30.079
It happens.
It was high on the wrist.

17:31.255 --> 17:34.170
Cause and manner
is homicide by strangulation.

17:35.176 --> 17:36.800
Good hunting, detective.

17:40.598 --> 17:42.583
"and anyone requiring
additional information

17:42.743 --> 17:45.216
"on cobra benefits
and pension payout as part

17:45.375 --> 17:47.193
"of the voluntary separation plan

17:47.738 --> 17:50.588
can schedule an appointment
with human resources."

17:51.063 --> 17:53.326
Some of you will migrate
into new positions

17:53.486 --> 17:55.260
while others will of course

17:55.940 --> 17:58.547
be moving on to other opportunities
beyond the Sun,

17:58.707 --> 18:01.712
but everyone in this room
has done excellent work

18:02.247 --> 18:04.704
and should be proud
of their contributions.

18:06.760 --> 18:09.356
- How many buyouts are there?
- That hasn't been determined yet.

18:09.516 --> 18:11.209
We're talking to the union later today.

18:11.369 --> 18:14.790
How'll this affect the upcoming contract
negotiations with the guild?

18:14.950 --> 18:17.142
Badly.
Kiss any raise good-bye.

18:17.562 --> 18:20.688
How come there's cuts in the newsroom
when the company's still profitable?

18:20.938 --> 18:23.147
There's nobody that feels
worse about this than I do.

18:24.103 --> 18:26.555
I've seen the excellent work
we've done here in Baltimore.

18:26.894 --> 18:29.236
The sooner we start
meeting with you individually,

18:29.396 --> 18:31.782
the sooner I can answer
all of your questions.

18:36.574 --> 18:38.689
- Not O'mara.
- Yeah.

18:39.282 --> 18:40.349
Aw, no.

18:42.287 --> 18:43.603
Good luck everybody.

18:44.646 --> 18:47.651
No increase in felonies
and a 1% bump in total crime.

18:52.053 --> 18:53.523
Do you vouch for these figures?

18:54.004 --> 18:55.554
- Sir?
- No increase in crime

18:55.714 --> 18:58.657
even after I cut you guys to the bone.
This is what you're telling me?

18:58.817 --> 19:00.722
Because the one thing I'm
asking of you guys--

19:00.882 --> 19:03.189
the one thing
that I'm asking above all--

19:03.349 --> 19:04.983
is that you bring me clean numbers.

19:05.822 --> 19:08.717
Yes, Mr. Mayor.
You made that clear.

19:11.671 --> 19:12.834
Very good then.

19:26.306 --> 19:27.390
Burrell is done.

19:27.789 --> 19:30.625
He just killed himself.
We leak the real stats,

19:30.785 --> 19:32.865
hold the cooked ones
in case he won't go quietly.

19:33.025 --> 19:34.457
And replace him with who?

19:34.865 --> 19:37.525
Rawls?
He came in with the same stats.

19:37.800 --> 19:40.091
If I know Bill Rawls,
he'll be calling over here as

19:40.251 --> 19:42.032
soon as he gets back to his office,

19:42.192 --> 19:44.318
telling us he warned Burrell
against cooking the books.

19:44.600 --> 19:47.817
The ministers won't live with Rawls.
Neither will Nerese.

19:47.977 --> 19:50.994
As acting commissioner,
they will for a few months at least

19:51.214 --> 19:53.020
if we've got a black
candidate to sell them.

19:53.180 --> 19:54.268
Daniels isn't ready.

19:54.428 --> 19:55.908
He's only been Colonel for a year.

19:56.068 --> 19:57.771
A year will do in a pinch.

19:59.954 --> 20:02.586
You float it with one of your
bunkies on Calvert street.

20:03.003 --> 20:04.204
See how it plays.

20:04.364 --> 20:07.098
Burrell reads that,
he'll shit melons.

20:07.258 --> 20:08.421
I fucking hope so.

20:09.325 --> 20:10.597
It's Baltimore.

20:12.211 --> 20:13.681
No one lives forever.

20:30.624 --> 20:31.785
Andreas, right?

20:34.890 --> 20:36.162
The Russian sent me.

20:39.163 --> 20:40.918
Need you to get a word to Vondas.

20:41.335 --> 20:42.739
He got a new friend.

20:43.222 --> 20:44.583
I never hear the name.

20:45.221 --> 20:47.298
Just let him know Marlo
came past with a gift.

20:51.212 --> 20:52.841
Be at you same time tomorrow.

21:11.812 --> 21:13.695
Any idea how long this could take?

21:14.504 --> 21:16.698
Don't know.
Might be here all day.

21:17.436 --> 21:19.326
I have meetings scheduled.

21:19.857 --> 21:22.122
We've got to lay
the foundation carefully,

21:22.282 --> 21:23.957
make it so the grand jurors understand

21:24.117 --> 21:27.168
all the ins and outs
so they don't get lost in the details.

21:32.285 --> 21:33.502
Mr. Howard?

21:39.932 --> 21:41.683
Is there any way
I could go earlier?

21:42.218 --> 21:44.101
If you're important enough, sure.

21:45.182 --> 21:48.480
I'm the vice president
of a major financial institution.

21:49.435 --> 21:50.842
Who the fuck isn't?

21:53.959 --> 21:56.789
Now, sir, directing your attention
to the document in your hand,

21:56.949 --> 21:58.778
is that also an account statement?

21:59.120 --> 22:00.143
Yes, it is,

22:00.422 --> 22:02.528
for a non-profit,
interest-bearing account,

22:02.879 --> 22:05.877
organizational,
with 5013 designation.

22:06.317 --> 22:10.461
Can begin by slowly
explaining in the most basic terms

22:10.621 --> 22:14.909
each of those things,
beginning with the word non-profit?

22:15.646 --> 22:18.201
- Hey, is box two open?
- Not yet.

22:18.361 --> 22:19.576
What about 3?

22:19.736 --> 22:21.723
Someone's killing homeless men.

22:22.647 --> 22:24.490
Medical examiner says so.

22:31.848 --> 22:33.931
Weird thing about my case, Bunk?

22:35.836 --> 22:38.990
Dead man was homeless,
but he had a red ribbon

22:39.633 --> 22:40.777
tied around his wrist.

22:40.937 --> 22:42.871
What does a homeless guy
have to remember

22:43.031 --> 22:45.708
that he should have a red ribbon
tied around his wrist?

22:49.774 --> 22:51.177
- Burlow.
- What?

22:51.833 --> 22:52.754
Nice out.

22:52.996 --> 22:55.925
Oh, like Chanel no. 5
comes out of your ass, moreland.

23:01.144 --> 23:04.010
If you got a problem,
then I got a problem.

23:04.456 --> 23:06.255
That's how the co-op work.

23:07.077 --> 23:08.507
What's the problem?

23:08.667 --> 23:10.197
I got too much money.

23:11.370 --> 23:15.131
Son, believe me,
you ain't alone.

